        <span style="mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:
minor-latin;color:#19150F">Sometimes, grantees will not weatherize rental homes or apartments unless the landlord agrees to pay for a portion of the cost or agrees to other conditions. The U.S. Department of Energy (DOE) also administers a program called the Low Income Weatherization Assistance Program (LIWAP) to weatherize homes or apartments of low income people. This program is usually run at the local level by Community Action Agencies. <o:p></o:p></span>
