        <span style="mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;color:#19150F">Renters are eligible for LIHEAP assistance. Many renters pay for their heating and/or cooling costs directly, while others pay these costs indirectly through their rent. In either case, you are eligible for LIHEAP help if you otherwise qualify. If you live in subsidized or public housing, you may be ineligible for LIHEAP assistance if heating and/or cooling and other utilities are included in your rent. If you live in subsidized or public housing, you may be eligible for LIHEAP assistance if you must pay for heating and/or cooling and utilities yourself. If you live in subsidized or public housing and (1) you are responsible for paying for heating and/or cooling and utilities and (2) receive a housing subsidy for all or part of your energy costs, the housing subsidy will most likely affect the size of your LIHEAP benefit.</span><span style="color:#2E74B5;mso-themecolor:accent1;mso-themeshade:191;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
